fields.name: New Jersey School Climate Survey Revision Draft AUGUST 2020

fields.description: This domain measures perceptions of school-wide academic expectations and norms related to students’ persistence and effort, academic investment, academic integrity, and equity and access.
fields.name: School-wide Academic Culture

fields.description: This domain focuses on perceptions of equity and fairness of behavior management and school rules and their application.
fields.name: Behavior Management

fields.description: This domain focuses on the extent to which parents and family members feel supported and engaged by the school to help foster student learning and growth, as well as parent/family involvement in the school community.
fields.name: Family Support and Engagement

fields.description: This domain focuses on perceptions of safety and procedures across school contexts and conditions.
fields.name: Safety

fields.description: This domain focuses on students’ personal sense of belonging and connectedness to the school community.
fields.name: Student Sense of Belonging

fields.description: Items in this domain capture perceptions of students’ involvement in negative interpersonal behaviors including physical and non-physical behaviors, such as those that occur in online and other virtual spaces. Students and staff are also asked about perceptions of student victimization based on students’ identity and background characteristics.
fields.name: Student Interpersonal Behaviors: Negative

fields.description: This domain focuses on perceptions of students’ prosocial and inclusive behaviors at the school. Student prosocial and inclusive behaviors include empathy, perspective taking, helping behaviors, and conflict resolution, as well as getting along well with students from diverse backgrounds and including students with disabilities in activities.
fields.name: Student Interpersonal Behaviors: Prosocial and Inclusive

fields.description: This domain focuses on the conditions in the school to support student voice, including listening to and valuing students’ ideas and opinions, student leadership, and student involvement in school activities and events.
fields.name: Student Voice and Involvement

fields.description: This domain focuses on the expressive supports provided by leadership to promote positive relationships, trust, and well-being among staff and administration. Supports focus on valuing diverse contributions of all staff, teaming, and open communication.
fields.name: Leadership Support

fields.description: This domain focuses on the district and school-level structures (e.g., policy, procedures, scheduling) as well as instrumental supports (e.g., resources, time, materials) that allow staff to be productive and perform effectively at work.
fields.name: Organizational Structures and Supports

fields.description: This domain focuses on staff sense of well-being, relationships with colleagues, and inclusion at work.
fields.name: Adult Social and Emotional Environment

fields.description: This domain focuses on the extent to which students are respected, cared for, and supported by adults in the school. This domain also captures stakeholders’ perceptions related to how adults provide a supportive and respectful environment for students of diverse social and cultural backgrounds.
fields.name: Adult-Student Relationships and Supports

fields.description: Items in this domain capture school-wide and instructional practices that promote the development of students’ social and emotional skills. Parents and families are also asked about perceptions of social and emotional supports their children receive as well as availability of resources to help family members talk to their children about emotions.
fields.name: Supports for Student Social and Emotional Learning
